<https://w3id.org/vibe-ontology/Anime> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Una forma di opera animata originaria principalmente del contesto mediatico giapponese."@it .
<https://w3id.org/vibe-ontology/Film> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Произведение движущихся изображений, созданное в рамках кинематографа."@ru .
<https://w3id.org/vibe-ontology/overlapsWith> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Indica che due Estetiche condividono elementi o associazioni significativi, senza che l'una sia sottogenere dell'altra. Questa proprietà è simmetrica."@it .
<https://w3id.org/vibe-ontology/ArtistRole> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "rol gespeeld door een agent als maker van of bijdrager aan artistieke productie."@nl .
<https://w3id.org/vibe-ontology/endYear> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#gYear> .
<https://w3id.org/vibe-ontology/coinedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Relates an Aesthetic to the Agent who coined or first named it."@en .
<https://w3id.org/vibe-ontology/Value> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Ценность"@ru .
<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#closeMatch> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/vibe-ontology/follows> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Indica che un'Estetica segue temporalmente o stilisticamente un'altra. Questa proprietà è transitiva."@it .
